Subtitle of Senate Bill 103
TO CREATE THE PHARMACY NONDISCRIMINATION ACT; TO REQUIRE PHARMACY
BENEFITS MANAGERS TO ACCEPT ANY PHARMACY OR PHARMACIST WILLING TO
ACCEPT RELEVANT AND REASONABLE TERMS OF PARTICIPATION; AND TO
DECLARE AN EMERGENCY.
______________________________________________________________________
Amendment No. 1 to Senate Bill 103
Amend Senate Bill 103 as originally introduced:
Add Senators Irvin, M. Johnson as cosponsors of the bill
AND
Page 5, delete lines 8 through 19, and substitute the following:
"(5) "Relevant and reasonable terms of participation" means
terms and conditions that:
(A) Are consistent with applicable state and federal law;
(B) Are consistent with industry standards; and
(C) Do not arbitrarily or discriminatorily exclude a
qualified pharmacy or pharmacist."
